Name: Cabin Repress
checklistText:
Cabin Repressurization


Assumption: LM is unstaged.

ECS Panel:
1.	Cabin relief & dump vlv (fwd) - AUTO 

2.	Cabin relief & dump vlv (ovhd) - AUTO 

3.	CABIN REPRESS vlv - AUTO

Panel 16:
	CB ECS: CABIN REPRESS - close
Panel 1,2:
	MASTER ALARM - on
Panel 1:
	CABIN warn lt - on
ECS Panel:
	CABIN REPRESS vlv opens

4.	PRESS REG A vlv - CABIN

Panel 1:
5.	MASTER ALARM pb/lt - reset

ECS Panel:
6.	PRESS REG B vlv - CABIN
Remarks:
	CABIN REPRESS vlv closes and CABIN warn lt goes off 
	when pressure reaches 4.4 to 5.0 psia.

Panel 1:
7.	CABIN warn lt - off

8.	Verify cabin pressure stabilizes at 4.8+/-0.2 psia

9.	Return to ECS Basic (unstaged), except:
	CABIN GAS RETURN vlv - AUTO before SUIT GAS DIVERTER
	vlv - PUSH CABIN

Steps.Text: set OVHD hatch Cabin Relief & Vent Vlv to AUTO
CABIN REPRESS vlv closes and cabin warn lt goes off when psia reaches 4.4 to 5.0
Verify cabin pressure stabilizes at approx 5.0
